main event: In June 1954, a civilian observer in Mooresville, Indiana reported seeing a white object with five sides in the sky at 2130 CST (N). The report included a photograph, and the source was a photographer by trade. The case was noted to be evaluated by Dr. Hynek.
interesting points: The observer reported seeing a white object with five sides, which is an unusual and specific shape for a UFO.
The sighting was reported by a civilian observer who was a photographer by trade, adding credibility to the report.
The case was to be evaluated by Dr. Hynek, a prominent ufologist known for his work with Project Blue Book and scientific approach to UFO investigations.
The report included two 8x10 photos of the unidentified flying object, indicating physical evidence of the sighting.

The report was part of the Project Blue Book special report no. 14, prepared by the Air Technical Intelligence Center at Wright-Patterson Air Force Base, adding an official and rigorous investigative element to the case.
sighted object: white object with five sides in the sky
